### List of open source projects involvement
* Qt. Provided Qt library compiled for [MIPS architecture](https://qt.gitorious.org/qt-creator/qt-creator/commit/7bae23b3a63e37d08ab3ab21b23b44e85560cb0c). How-to article about using [tooltips with custom data models](http://qt-project.org/wiki/Show_tooltips_for_long_entries_of_your_custom_model).
* [Nemo mobile](https://wiki.merproject.org/wiki/Nemo). Fixed several bugs, that are already included in the release.
* [Zonerama](https://code.google.com/p/zonerama/). Created a [patch](https://code.google.com/p/zonerama/source/detail?r=38) that allows to use the software after installation.
* [KFZcheck](http://wiki.yourse.de/doku.php?id=python:kfzcheck). Created list-file that contains description of Russian [licence plates](http://maemo.org/packages/view/kfzcheck/).
* [libdc1394](http://damien.douxchamps.net/ieee1394/libdc1394/). A patch that allows to use FLIR A40 thermal [infrared camera in Linux](http://kit.origo.ethz.ch/wiki/flir_a40_and_libdc1394). The cameras that do not follow the IIDC specification are not officially supported by _libdc1394_. Because of this the patch is rejected by maintainers.
